	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Feb 12th 11:50 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122149><span id= >Balgriffin</span></a><br><span id=notbold>14 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Umm, I hate to be the bearer of bad news, but no, going to misty thicket probably was not your best move.&nbsp;&nbsp;Here is why I say that:<br><br>Misty thicket has an ok newbie zone, but once you make it to 6th or 7th level and try to head out to the other side of &quot;the wall&quot;, those blasted guards are MAJOR kill stealers.. and yet never seem to be there when you need them the most.  <br><br>Lets move up a few levels, and you begin to eyeball Runnyeye.  My advice... DON'T.  Runnyeye is a deadly place for low level characters, even assuming you could get a group there (not a lot of people up there...)<br><br>G-Fay on the other hand, has an okay newbie zone, but then at 6 or 7 you can head up to the Orc Lift and get bound there, then play with the orcs on Orc Hill.  Collect enough of those orc belts and do the Orc Belt quest for money, armor and experience.<br><br>Then when you move up a bit, head into Crushbone.  Crushbone has a LOT more people there, and getting a group is far easier, and it is FAR safer than Runnyeye.  Just be mindful of the trains...<br><br>After you outgrow Crushbone, you can then head to ButcherBlock Mountains and hunt there quite easily.<br><br>Misty thicket limits you far too much and those blasted guards are a pain (VERY irritating to bearly survive a fight, have the mob running and almost dead, just to have one of those Runt Guards Kill Steal the mob just as you are about to land the finishing blow!)<br><br>Good luck, if it were me, I would get a return port to G-fay...<br><br><br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
