	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122149><span id= >Balgriffin</span></a><br><span id=notbold>14 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well, you researched the armor.. good! Because the best way to learn is to do it yourself! But here is some help.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>Yes there are other sites, and a great one is www.eqdiva.com this is a site dedicated just to bards, and has a lot of good infomation.<br><br>Key points of a bard... its about the music my friend!  I almost quit my Bard at 17, because at one yellow bubble shy of 18, I spent almost TWO weeks trying to get to 18.  Every single time I would get close.. WHAM dead.  It did not seem to matter if I was grouped or not, EVERY single time I got close .. POW - Dead.<br><br>Well I quit playing the bard for a bit, then one day I came back to it... now it is my main, and I am loving it.  The problem, I was trying to play as if I was a warrior... I was not using my songs very well.  So I researched my songs, took some time to ponder the best way to use them, and from there never looked back!<br><br>When you get your First Brass Song (DDD) find a SAFE spot and PRATICE that song until it is MAXED, then when you get to 26, Fear kiting will be a blast.  <br><br>Followed, by the next level.. Charm Kiting!<br><br>Bards can solo well, and are great in a group, although they often don't realize JUST how much having a bard helps until they DON'T have one anylonger...<br><br>Allakhazam, Casters Realm and EQ Diva.. those are Three great sites for your research.  <br><br>Never let the music die!<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Feb 12 11:06:27 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
