	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=101310502668142>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101310502668142>RE: Weapons?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101310502668142#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Feb 7th 2:06 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=113466><span id=Sage>rutkoskyd</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>62 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The beauty of Everquest is the versatility of the game.&nbsp;&nbsp;To answer your question... there is no answer.  Try new things, experiment with new weapons, and most of all have a great time doing it.<br><br>Now, since I know for a fact that wasn't what you wanted to hear, here's the real answer:  Many people wield piercing weapons either because of class limitations or because of the low delay.  1hs is one of the more versatile weapon classes in terms of weapons available, and the fact that (as a bard) you will get dual wield at level 17, it seems like 1hs would be a decent bet.  2hs-ers can do some serious damage but are usually handicapped by a very long delay.  Typically you will see characters with a much higher str stat wielding the 2hs.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>1 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f101317245071889>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=101317245071889>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101317245071889>RE: Weapons?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101317245071889#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Feb 8th 8:50 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1056 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.13]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I agree with everything Rutkoskyd says.&nbsp;&nbsp;I would like to add to that:<br><br>The choice of weapons can be limited by class also.  Rogues, for example, can use any 1 handed weapon, but in order to use backstab (the ultimate rogue melee skill) a rogue must have a piercing weapon in the primary hand.<br><br>Clerics are pretty much restricted to blunt weapons.<br><br>Shamans use piercing and blunt.<br><br>Druids use blunt and scimitars (1hs).<br><br>You get the picture.<br><br>Piercing weapons are popular due to their low delay, as you said. So, many folks use them as off-hand weapons.  Also, many piercing weapons, at higher level, get some decent procs.  <br><br>In the end a player should use the weapon that is most effective for his/her playing style.  Warriors, with critical hit ability, probably will want weapons that deal out a large amount of damage per strike.<br><br>Bards, who do not have critical strike, will likely want weapons with a lower delay but a high damage to delay ratio.  This way the bard hits for less per strike but hits more frequently. Over time this adds up.  Weapons that have DOT spells on them work, too, in this role.  This is, of course, my opinion.  I have not played a bard long but have played several other classes into their 20's and above.<br><br>Then there is the question of aggro management. Cause or heal too much damage and you are going to become the main object of any MOBs desire.  Keep that in mind when choosing your weapons, too.<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr>
