	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=101199076625856>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101199076625856>RE: wall</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=101199076625856#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Jan 25th 4:34 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=50234><span id=Sage>Hooray</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>66 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.71]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>At L11 near Queynos the best choice is probably hunting gnolls in Blackburrow. Gnolls come in anything from L5 to L15. Beware of the ever present trains, though.<br>Alternatively you can go to Everfrost and get a mammoth calf group.<br><br>As Brusco's goes, i personally never used it much. It is nice for pulling around your level, but if you have a decent weapon you will gain more by twisting Jonathan's, Chant of Battle and Hymn of Restoration.<br>In a group, replace Jonathans's with Anthem.<br><br>Nothe that a lot of people swear on twisting Brusco's in, its a matter of personal preference. Also the weapon you use makes a huge difference in usefulness. I twinked my bard with a crystal spider fang at like 14 and the damage output from this makes Brusco's pretty insignificant.<br><br>One other application is kiting a mob with Brusco's, which is difficult to master, and usually not very effective. However, if you see you are just barely on the loosing side in a fight, kick in selos, run away a bit, use brusco's, twist with hymn and selo's, always keeping out of the MOBs range. Usually you can change the odds far enough to win the fight.</p>&nbsp;<br>Nindor<br>L65 Dwarven Cleric on Zebuxoruk<br>Stone</td></td></tr>
